## Two types of validators
As you know currently there are two types of validators: 
1) first makes their own evaluation of subnets quality and sets weights based on it (like OTF, Taostats and etc)
2) and second one sets weights based on the votes of stakers: if you stake with this validator you can vote for subnets and the more stake you have the more powerful your vote is

I believe that we're building something really great here and the recent benchmarks update doesn't lie about it. For that reason we have 2 or more percent of weight from most of the validators of the first type. Unfortunately, there are still vote-based validators, where weights usually get not the best subnet, but the richest one.

## Vote-based validators
And here is where we need your support. We staked and voted on our own and for that reason we got 1.5% of weights from tao5 (the biggest vote-based validator), but there're also other vote-based validators, who currently set low weights to SN32 and make our overall weights lower.

So, if you're a miner or like what we're doing here in SN32 and want to support us, your votes will be really appreciated, even if it's only a few hundreds of tao (it still can make a difference). Here is a list of validators, who has vote-based system:

# Validator Update - Major - v3.8
@itsai・32 
Today we're releasing on testnet v3.8. 
## V3.8
### AI + human texts 
Before that we had fully ai, fully human and human + ai texts (where first part was human and we ask LLMs to write a completion). Now, during validation we also adding AI + human samples to make it more balanced, here is how it works:
1) Take human text and split it to 3 parts
2) summarize middle part with LLM
3) ask LLM to complete the full text, given first, third part and summarization of the middle
4) take generated middle part and the third part as sample
### Augs adjustment
In v3.8 we added space deletion aug and a little adjusted the proportion of previous augs. We also lower a minimum amount of words in one text up to 35 words.
### LLMs pool updated with up to 120b models
We updated the LLMs pool with fresh models and also added huge LLMs (llama3.3:70b, command-r-plus:104b, mistral-large:123b and others) to gain maximum quality of open-sourced models. Updated LLMS pool will consist of more than 30 different models, taked from the top of LLM arena.
## ❗️Validation requirements update❗️
Previously the minimum requirements for validating was 24gb VRAM (like RTX4090). With new big LLMs in our pool, you have to have at least 80gb VRAM and 1T of disk space. We recommend to use A100, because we've tested on it and it works fine. 

You also need to update your ollama to support all provided models: 
```
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
pm2 restart ollama
```
To check that everything is okay you can pull our testnet v3.8 branch, run command for data generation (`python3 detection/validator/data_generator.py`) and check that there appeared a file generated_data.csv after 30-60min (you can monitor progress by logs).
## Timeline
As for now we releasing only on testnet (v3.8 branch in our github)
We are going to release it on mainnet in about a week, most probably on 4 Feb.
